---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Services - SkanPay"
  description="Explore SkanPay services for in-store QR payments, payment gateway integration, merchant onboarding, and partner support."
  activePath="/services/"
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Services</p>
    <h1>QR payment services for merchants and payment partners</h1>
    <p>SkanPay supports conversations around in-store QR payment acceptance, gateway workflows, merchant onboarding, and wallet or loyalty partnerships.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="grid two">
      <article class="card accent">
        <h3>In-store QR payments</h3>
        <p>Help merchants present a simple scan-and-pay checkout option that customers can understand quickly.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Payment gateway integration</h3>
        <p>Support technical and operational planning for QR payment flows, transaction status, and confirmation handling.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Merchant onboarding</h3>
        <p>Shape the practical steps stores need to get started, train staff, and explain QR payment at checkout.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card accent">
        <h3>Loyalty and wallet partnerships</h3>
        <p>Connect payment conversations with apps that already have customer relationships, rewards, or stored wallet behavior.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section split">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Operational fit</p>
      <h2>Keep the checkout experience understandable</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">A QR payment service only works when the merchant, customer, and payment partner all know what is supposed to happen next.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="split-panel">
      <h3>Service conversations can include</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Store-level QR payment use cases</li>
        <li>Customer scan and authorization flow</li>
        <li>Merchant transaction confirmation needs</li>
        <li>General reporting and settlement expectations</li>
        <li>Partner or wallet integration planning</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
